thought:
**Determining the New Administrative Unit for "Xã Nhơn Phong"**

Okay, let's break this down systematically. The user has provided an old address, "Xã Nhơn Phong, Thị xã An Nhơn, Tỉnh Bình Định," and I need to identify the corresponding new administrative unit.

First, I recognized that "Tỉnh Bình Định" is likely a crucial piece.  I immediately thought of the province resolutions (60-NQ/TW) to see if there were any mergers or name changes. Sure enough, "Tỉnh Bình Định" was merged with "Tỉnh Gia Lai," now known as "Tỉnh Gia Lai." This is the first key piece of the puzzle.

Next, I need to focus on "Xã Nhơn Phong". Since Bình Định merged into Gia Lai, I needed to search resolutions related to Gia Lai to determine if there are changes. I scanned through various resolutions but noticed that resolution 1664/NQ-UBTVQH15 seemed the most promising with the title "Sắp xếp các đơn vị hành chính cấp xã của tỉnh Gia Lai."

Within this resolution, line 111 jumped out at me.  It clearly stated that "Xã Nhơn Phong" was consolidated to form "phường An Nhơn Bắc". Bingo! This is the core of the solution.

To confirm, I needed to cross-reference with the list of new wards. I then checked the "New wards" data for "phường An Nhơn Bắc" under "Tỉnh Gia Lai".  I found a matching entry: `{"ward_code":"21925","ward_name":"Phường An Nhơn Bắc","province_name":"Tỉnh Gia Lai"}`.  This confirmed my findings.

Finally, I will create the JSON output with a high degree of confidence. I also re-checked other lines in 1664/NQ-UBTVQH15 to ensure there were no other relevant mentions but found none.
I am confident that `phường An Nhơn Bắc` is the new administrative unit for "Xã Nhơn Phong".
